The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 February is 39,974 (4,626.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 February, there were 732 new confirmed cases (84.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 February, there were 870 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 16% (138 fewer cases).
